&lt;p&gt;US President Donald Trump announced that a &quot;complete and total&quot; ceasefire had been reached between Israel and Iran, aiming to bring an end to the 12-day-long conflict, shortly after both countries had issued fresh threats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An Iranian official confirmed Tehran had consented to the truce, though there was no immediate statement from Israel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to a senior White House source, Israel agreed to the ceasefire on the condition that Iran halts further attacks. The agreement was mediated by Trump during a phone conversation with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trump implied that the parties would be given time to finish their ongoing operations, after which the ceasefire would take effect gradually.&lt;/p&gt;
